      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve Codex web credits-only refresh",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve authorized Codex web dashboard snapshots when credits are present but usage-limit windows are absent\n- synthesize a credits-only Codex `UsageSnapshot` with the attached dashboard identity, matching existing CLI/OAuth partial-result behavior\n- add regression coverage for the authorized credits-only web dashboard path\n\n## Why\nFixes #1204.\n\nThe Codex web strategy already verifies dashboard ownership before attachment, but it still threw `.missingUsage` when `dashboard.toUsageSnapshot(...)` returned nil. That made a useful authenticated dashboard response with credits/account data look like a failed provider fetch. CLI and OAuth already preserve credits-only responses, so this brings the web path in line with those sources.\n\n## Validation\n- `swift test --filter CodexWebDashboardStrategyAuthorityTests`\n- `make check`\n- `TZ=UTC swift test`\n",
